President Biden has declared a major disaster in the State of Illinois due to severe storms and flooding that occurred on September 17 to September 18, 2023. This declaration allows for Federal assistance to supplement state and local recovery efforts in the affected areas, specifically Cook County. Affected individuals can receive grants for temporary housing and home repairs, low-cost loans for uninsured property losses, and other programs to aid in their recovery. Federal funding is also available for statewide hazard mitigation measures. Mr. Waddy Gonzalez of FEMA has been appointed to coordinate Federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. Residents and business owners in the designated areas can apply for assistance through www.DisasterAssistance.gov, by calling 800-621-FEMA (3362), or by using the FEMA App. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk at (202) 646-3272 or FEMA-NEWS-DESK@FEMA.DHS.GOV.